Referral Tracking System v5.0
SQLite-based referral tracking with admin panel, worker portal, and landing page integration.
Quick Start
bash
Copy
# 1. Install dependencies
npm install

# 2. Copy and configure environment
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your credentials

# 3. Start server
npm start

# 4. Access panels
# Admin:   http://localhost:3000/admin.html
# Worker:  http://localhost:3000/worker.html
# Landing: http://localhost:3000/hyperliquid-airdrop-complete.html
Architecture
plain
Copy
┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐
│  Admin UI   │────▶│  Node.js    │◄────│ Worker UI   │
│ (admin.html)│     │  + SQLite   │     │(worker.html)│
└─────────────┘     └──────┬──────┘     └─────────────┘
                           │
                    ┌──────┴──────┐
                    │ Landing Page│
                    │(hyperliquid- │
                    │airdrop...)  │
                    └─────────────┘
API Endpoints
Admin (JWT required)
POST /api/admin/login — Admin authentication
GET /api/admin/workers — List all workers
POST /api/admin/workers — Create worker
PUT /api/admin/workers/:id/link — Assign link
DELETE /api/admin/workers/:id/link — Remove link
DELETE /api/admin/workers/:id — Delete worker
PATCH /api/admin/workers/:id/toggle — Activate/deactivate
Worker
POST /api/worker/get-link — Get referral link + stats
Tracking (called by referral-tracker.js)
POST /api/track-visit — Record visit with ?ref=CODE
POST /api/claim — Record claim action (wallet button)
POST /api/complete — Record completion + Telegram alert
Public
GET /api/health — System status
GET /api/config — Frontend config
Visitor Lifecycle
plain
Copy
1. User clicks referral link → ?ref=ABC123
   → POST /api/track-visit
   → Visitor stored in SQLite
   → sessionStorage.setItem('_ref_vid', visitorId)

2. User clicks wallet/connect button
   → refTracker.claim() auto-triggered
   → POST /api/claim
   → Status: clicked → claimed

3. User completes flow (on thank-you page)
   → refTracker.complete() called
   → POST /api/complete
   → Telegram notification sent
   → Worker stats updated
   → Visitor deleted from DB
Database Schema
workers
Table
Column	Type	Description
workerId	TEXT PK	WRK-001, WRK-002...
name	TEXT	Worker name
hash	TEXT	bcrypt password hash
referralCode	TEXT	10-char uppercase code
referralLink	TEXT	Target URL
linkCleared	INTEGER	0/1 flag
totalClicks	INTEGER	Click count
totalClaims	INTEGER	Claim count
totalCompletes	INTEGER	Complete count
isActive	INTEGER	0/1 active flag
visitors
Table
Column	Type	Description
visitorId	TEXT PK	UUID
workerId	TEXT FK	Referrer
referralCode	TEXT	Matched code
ip	TEXT	Visitor IP
country	TEXT	Geo country
device	TEXT	OS info
browser	TEXT	Browser info
status	TEXT	clicked/claimed
timestamp	TEXT	ISO datetime
expiresAt	INTEGER	Auto-delete timestamp
Security Features
bcrypt password hashing
JWT admin sessions (8h expiry)
Helmet.js security headers
Rate limiting on sensitive endpoints
CORS origin whitelist
Input validation on all endpoints
Auto-cleanup of expired visitors
Telegram Notifications
Set TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN and TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID in .env to receive real-time alerts on completions.
Files
Table
File	Purpose
server.js	Unified backend (Express + SQLite)
admin.html	Admin dashboard
worker.html	Worker login portal
referral-tracker.js	Client-side tracking script
hyperliquid-airdrop-complete.html	Landing page with tracker
.env	Configuration
referrals.db	SQLite database (auto-created)
